 ![Samir Canales Molina, and Bravlio Galeano Ayala](https://a57.foxnews.com/static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2026/01/1200/675/north-carolina-teen-murders-illegal-immigrant-sanctuary-ice-002.jpg?ve=1&tl=1)

Samir Canales Molina, left, and Bravlio Galeano Ayala were killed, and DHS says sanctuary policies and ignored ICE detainers allowed a criminal illegal immigrant to remain free before the deadly attack. (Department of Homeland Security)

The killings come as federal authorities ramp up pressure on jurisdictions that [refuse to honor ICE detainers](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/immigration/enforcement), a practice DHS says allows criminal aliens to cycle back onto the streets.

ICE reported in November that [local authorities across North Carolina](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/us-regions/southeast/north-carolina) failed to honor nearly 1,400 detainers, instead releasing criminal aliens back into communities.

